race.comment: TISHMAN (1) resumes for a top metro stable and kicking off at the mile won't be an issue. He's raced well in stronger than this and has had three jumpouts, placing the latest. Maps okay and the 3kg claim brings him right into it. MISS CASTELVECCHIO (14) peaks and was only beaten 1.4L over this trip at Caulfield Heath. Has a wide gate to contend with, but this is winnable with average luck. TRIPLE TIME (4) is a stablemate to the top selection and on the improve. Has been backed off the map both starts and will get every chance from an inside barrier. JUMPINMYCAR (2) also brings a strong Maiden win, and the extra metres will suit him.
